# C++ engine (Cursor rule)

- Use C++23 as the required language level; no C++20 compatibility shims.
- Follow [`docs/cpp-style.md`](../../docs/cpp-style.md) for naming, layout, CMake targets, and unit-test aggregate literals.
- Keep `engine/core` standard-library-only; platform work behind `engine/platform`; graphics behind renderer/RHI.
- Prefer RAII, value types, explicit ownership, and `mirakana::` for public API.
- Treat removed Dear ImGui shell implementation as historical evidence only; runtime game UI uses public `mirakana::ui` contracts and must not depend on UI middleware.
- The optional Windows-native `MK_editor` shell is active through the dependency-free `desktop-editor` lane; do not recreate removed SDL3 shell sources. The current Windows D3D12 viewport/material visible texture compositor remains private under `editor/src`; future Vulkan/Metal parity or broader material-preview GPU parity needs focused validation.
- Use `pwsh -NoProfile -ExecutionPolicy Bypass -File tools/check-toolchain.ps1`, `tools/cmake.ps1`, `tools/ctest.ps1`, and `tools/check-tidy.ps1` per [`AGENTS.md`](../../AGENTS.md).
- Use focused target builds/tests while iterating, then `tools/validate.ps1` at the slice-closing gate.

See [`.claude/rules/cpp-engine.md`](../../.claude/rules/cpp-engine.md) for the full scoped rule.
